external_knowledge:
- In the context of the forum, 'shines brightest' metaphorically refers to the topic with the highest view count and the most recent activity;
- 'Gem' and 'treasure' are used metaphorically to represent the topic titles;
- 'Sparkle of its view count' and 'glow of its recent activity' are metaphorical expressions referring to the view_count and last_activity columns respectively.

sql:
SELECT topic_title, creator_id, category, view_count
FROM topics
ORDER BY view_count DESC;

SELECT category, AVG(view_count) AS average_views
FROM forums
GROUP BY category;

external_knowledge:
- 'active forums' refer to forums with discussions and activity;
- 'typical engagement level' can be understood as the average view count per topic;
- 'most popular file in terms of downloads' implies the highest download count among all files in the forum.

sql:
SELECT forum_name
FROM forums
WHERE forum_id = 1;

SELECT t.topic_title, f.forum_name
FROM topics t
INNER JOIN forums f ON t.forum_id = f.forum_id;

SELECT COUNT(forum_id) AS forum_count
FROM forums
WHERE category = 'quantum physics';

SELECT COUNT(topic_id) AS total_topics
FROM topics
WHERE forum_id = 1;

SELECT filename
FROM files
WHERE upload_date > '2023-03-01';

SELECT topic_title
FROM topics
WHERE topic_id = 1;

SELECT filename
FROM files
WHERE download_count = (SELECT MAX(download_count) FROM files);

SELECT SUM(view_count) AS total_views 
FROM files 
WHERE filesize LIKE '1% Kbytes';

SELECT forum_name, last_activity
FROM forums
ORDER BY last_activity DESC;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT forum_id) AS forum_count
FROM forums
WHERE category = 'spirituality' AND view_count > 50;
